<!DOCTYPE task PUBLIC "-//OASIS//DTD DITA Task//EN" "task.dtd">
<task id="adding_steps_to_your_screenshot">
    <title>Adding Steps to your Screenshot</title>
    <shortdesc>You can guide a user through a set of instructions by adding steps to your
        screenshot.</shortdesc>
    <taskbody>
        <prereq
            conref="adding_text_to_an_image.dita#adding_text_to_an_image/prereq_completed_print_screen"
            id="prereq_mwq_wvy_vpb"/>
        <context id="context_ahp_fcy_vpb">
            <p>As a technical writer, adding steps to your screenshot can help guide your user
                through your documentation. This can be accomplished by using the
                    <uicontrol>Steps</uicontrol> tool.</p>
            <p>In addition, it is possible to change the type, color and shape of the steps.</p>
        </context>
        <steps>
            <step>
                <cmd>Select <uicontrol>Step</uicontrol>.<image
                        href="file:/C:/Users/n_bos/Desktop/Snagit%20Screenshots/Toolbar%20-%20Steps.png"
                        id="image_jfh_4cy_vpb"/></cmd>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd importance="optional">Modify the step style.</cmd>
                <info><ul id="ul_x2c_gwm_5pb">
                        <li>Change the color.</li>
                        <li>Change the shape.</li>
                        <li>Change the type.</li>
                    </ul><image
                        href="file:/C:/Users/n_bos/Desktop/Snagit%20Screenshots/Steps%20Properties%20-%20Empty.png"
                        id="image_zvv_ycy_vpb"/></info>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>Click on the screenshot to place your steps.<image
                        href="file:/C:/Users/n_bos/Desktop/Snagit%20Screenshots/StepsPlace.jpg"
                        id="image_ekc_cdy_vpb"/></cmd>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>Save your file.</cmd>
            </step>
        </steps>
        <result id="result_my5_fcy_vpb">After completing these steps you will have steps placed on
            your screenshot.</result>
    </taskbody>
</task>
